content.original: The crowd is not cheering for us, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: The crowd is not cheering for us, Commander.
content.content: Что-то толпа нас не очень приветствует, командир.

content.original: Hah! Showed those warriors our abilites, Commander. Great job!
content.prevOriginal: Hah! Showed those warriors our abilites, Commander. Great job!
content.content: Хех! Показали этим двоим, на что мы способны. Отличная работа!

content.original: I think we've just rained on the Trial of Position with this loss.
content.prevOriginal: I think we've just rained on the Trial of Position with this loss.
content.content: Кажется, испытание положения удалось, только не в нашу пользу.

content.original: BattleMech Trial of Position. Ready! GO!
content.prevOriginal: BattleMech Trial of Position. Ready! GO!
content.content: Испытание положения на боевых мехах. Приготовиться! НАЧАЛИ!

content.original: Last Minute Replacements
content.prevOriginal: Last Minute Replacements
content.content: Замена в последнюю минуту

As they haven't had their Trial of Position, we can not allow them to fight this match. We would like you to particpate as their proxies instead, saving {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym}'s honor, while also showing our sibko what it means to be a Warrior.

content.original: So, clean up the mess AND give away the credit. What a raw situation. At least the MRB knows the deal.
content.prevOriginal: So, clean up the mess AND give away the credit. What a raw situation. At least the MRB knows the deal.
content.content: Итак, навести порядок. но чтобы почести за это получили другие. Нестандартная ситуация. По крайней мере, MRB в курсе.

content.original: Defeat the duelists
content.prevOriginal: Defeat the duelists
content.content: Победите дуэлянтов

content.original: Looks like those expert warriors are waiting for you. Good luck, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: Looks like those expert warriors are waiting for you. Good luck, Commander.
content.content: Похоже, эти опытные мехвоины уже ждут вас. Удачи, командир.

content.original: And down they go!
content.prevOriginal: And down they go!
content.content: И им пришёл конец.

content.original: Let's get you out of here, Commander. It couldn't be helped.
content.prevOriginal: Let's get you out of here, Commander. It couldn't be helped.
content.content: Давайте вытаскивать вас отсюда, командир. Ничего не поделаешь.

content.original: Finally! We thought you both had chickened out.
content.prevOriginal: Finally! We thought you both had chickened out.
content.content: Наконец-то! Мы уже подумали, что вы оба струсили.

content.original: Words Hurt
content.prevOriginal: Words Hurt
content.content: Слова ранят

content.original: A {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Trinary Leader has taken issue with a recently released report on military inefficencies. She has demanded a duel to fight those allegations. We would like to hire you to represent our allegations, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: A {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Trinary Leader has taken issue with a recently released report on military inefficencies. She has demanded a duel to fight those allegations. We would like to hire you to represent our allegations, Commander.
content.content: Лидер тринария {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} выразила несогласие с недавно опубликованным отчетом о неэффективности военных. Она потребовала дуэли, оспаривая обвинения. Мы хотели бы нанять вас для защиты наших доводов, командир.

content.original: I just don't know, Commander. When people say they want to 'fight' allegations, it's not meant to be a real fight. These {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Clanners are crazy. Everything is a fight for them.
content.prevOriginal: I just don't know, Commander. When people say they want to 'fight' allegations, it's not meant to be a real fight. These {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Clanners are crazy. Everything is a fight for them.
content.content: Я уже просто не знаю, командир. Когда люди говорят, что хотят «сражаться» с заявлениями, это не должно подразумевать реальное сражение. Эти кланнеры из {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} с ума посходили. Для них что угодно может быть поводом размахивать кулаками.

content.original: Defeat the duelists
content.prevOriginal: Defeat the duelists
content.content: Победите дуэлянтов

content.original: The duelists are out there on the other side of the arena. Good luck, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: The duelists are out there on the other side of the arena. Good luck, Commander.
content.content: Дуэлянты на другой стороне арены. Удачи, командир.

content.original: There we go. Issue settled. Back to the dropship, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: There we go. Issue settled. Back to the dropship, Commander.
content.content: Ну вот. Вопрос решен. Возвращайтесь к дропшипу, командир.

content.original: This isn't how things should be. You shouldn't be able to repress the truth like this.
content.prevOriginal: This isn't how things should be. You shouldn't be able to repress the truth like this.
content.content: Неправильно всё это. Нельзя силой подавлять правду.

content.original: You can retract that report now, or when your mechs are flaming scrapheaps.
content.prevOriginal: You can retract that report now, or when your mechs are flaming scrapheaps.
content.content: У вас есть выбор: либо отзовите этот отчёт сейчас, либо после того, как ваши мехи превратятся в пылающие обломки.

content.original: Yearly Tussle
content.prevOriginal: Yearly Tussle
content.content: Ежегодная схватка

content.original: Every year {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} in {TGT_SYSTEM.name} continues a historic tradition with {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym}. We both field mercenaries in a Trial of Possession, and whoever wins claims a year's worth of good food and fine wines. Our usual mercenaries who help us were recently and unexpectedly wiped out by a misjump, so we have come to you for help.
content.prevOriginal: Every year {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} in {TGT_SYSTEM.name} continues a historic tradition with {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym}. Наши обычные наёмники, которые нам помогали, недавно неожиданно скончались из-за кривого прыжка, поэтому мы обратились к вам за помощью.

content.original: What do you think? Maybe we can get some of this good food and fine wine as part of the deal!
content.prevOriginal: What do you think? Maybe we can get some of this good food and fine wine as part of the deal!
content.content: Что думаете? Может, мы сможем включить в договор часть той хорошей еды и хорошие вина!

content.original: Defeat Duelists
content.prevOriginal: Defeat Duelists
content.content: Одолейте дуэлянтов

content.original: Our employers have won this every year for the past four years. No pressure, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: Our employers have won this every year for the past four years. No pressure, Commander.
content.content: Наши работодатели побеждали здесь каждый год на протяжении последних четырёх лет. Просто говорю, никакого давления.

content.original: You did it! Time to organise the party. We can't let all this go to waste!
content.prevOriginal: You did it! Time to organise the party. We can't let all this go to waste!
content.content: У вас получилось! Повод закатить вечеринку. Нельзя же всему этому банкету позволить пропасть!

content.original: Our employers can't expect to win this every year I suppose.
content.prevOriginal: Our employers can't expect to win this every year I suppose.
content.content: Надеюсь, наш наниматель не думал, что он вечно будет одерживать победу.

content.original: We're ravenous, Mercs. We're going to chew through your mechs, then enjoy the feast!
content.prevOriginal: We're ravenous, Mercs. We're going to chew through your mechs, then enjoy the feast!
content.content: Знаете, мы вообще-то весьма прожорливые. И я лично откушу кусок от каждого вашего меха. Запируем, господа!

content.original: All Eyes On
content.prevOriginal: All Eyes On
content.content: Под пристальным вниманием

content.original: Commander, {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} forces have always been a bother, always claiming to be superior to ours. So we arranged for a Trial of Grievance against {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym}, and bargined for you to fight on our behalf as a slight to them. They're enraged at the implications of this, and we're more than happy to exploit it for ourselves. For the Glory of the Clan, show {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} that even our hired mercenaries are stronger than they are.
content.prevOriginal: Commander, {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} forces have always been a bother, always claiming to be superior to ours. Поэтому мы устроили испытание обиды против {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} и сторговались, чтобы вы сражались от нашего имени, чтобы уязвить их гордость. Они в ярости от подтекста этого, и мы с радостью воспользуемся этим в своих интересах. Во славу нашего клана, покажите {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name}, что даже наши наёмники сильнее их.

content.original: It's going to be a Circle of Equals. I hope they bring their own supply, because I don't know if we have enough sugar packets onboard.
content.prevOriginal: It's going to be a Circle of Equals. I hope they bring their own supply, because I don't know if we have enough sugar packets onboard.
content.content: Это будет круг равных. Ну, или почти равных. В общем, оппоненту не позавидуешь.

content.original: Zellbrigen
content.prevOriginal: Zellbrigen
content.content: Зеллбриген

content.original: Here we go, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: Here we go, Commander.
content.content: Ну, поехали, командир.

content.original: Time to show this pilot a thing or two.
content.prevOriginal: Time to show this pilot a thing or two.
content.content: Пора показать этому пилоту где RAC'и зимуют.

content.original: A Circle of Equals well fought, Commander. We have brought glory to the Clan
content.prevOriginal: A Circle of Equals well fought, Commander. We have brought glory to the Clan
content.content: Интересный круг равных получился, командир. Мы принесли славу нашему клану.

content.original: Well at least it was not a Trial of Possession.
content.prevOriginal: Well at least it was not a Trial of Possession.
content.content: Ну, хотя бы хорошо, что это было не испытание владения.

content.original: A Taste For War
content.prevOriginal: A Taste For War
content.content: Пристрастие к войне

content.original: A {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Warrior has issued you a Trial of Grievance through us, Commander. It's a good opportunity to show our Sibkos how mercenaries fight, so we'll pay you if you win. Now, will {COMPANY.CompanyName} be remembered for their glorious fight, or forgotten?
content.prevOriginal: A {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Warrior has issued you a Trial of Grievance through us, Commander. content.content: Воин {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} через нас объявляет вам испытание обиды, командир. Это хорошая возможность показать нашим сибко, как сражаются наёмники. Мы заплатим вам, если вы победите. Итак, запомнят ли {COMPANY.CompanyName} за славный бой или же предадут забвению?

content.original: I wonder what we did to get this grievance? Was it that stuff I did on Tuesday?
content.prevOriginal: I wonder what we did to get this grievance? Was it that stuff I did on Tuesday?
content.content: Интересно, что мы такого сделали, чтобы на нас обиделись? Это из-за того, что я написал в прошлый четверг?

content.original: Destroy Enemy Warrior
content.prevOriginal: Destroy Enemy Warrior
content.content: Уничтожьте вражеского воина

content.original: Here we go, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: Here we go, Commander.
content.content: Ну, поехали, командир.

content.original: The {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Warrior awaits yor advance.
content.prevOriginal: The {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Warrior awaits yor advance.
content.content: Воин {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} ждёт, когда ты приблизишься.

content.original: Good job, Commander! That should put to rest any doubts on our skill.
content.prevOriginal: Good job, Commander! That should put to rest any doubts on our skill.
content.content: Отличная работа, командир! Это должно развеять все сомнения в нашем мастерстве.

content.original: We will lick our wounds Commander. Hopefully this doesn't reflect to poorly on our service.
content.prevOriginal: We will lick our wounds Commander. Hopefully this doesn't reflect to poorly on our service.
content.content: Ничего, раны залечатся, командир. Надеюсь, это не отразится слишком плохо на нашей службе.

content.original: Challenge Accepted
content.prevOriginal: Challenge Accepted
content.content: Вызов принят

content.original: Our battles with {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} in and around {TGT_SYSTEM.name} have been a waste of resources. {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} has issued us a Trial of Possession for this small area of the conflict. It will be a one-on-one battle in a Circle of Equals with you taking our place, ostensibly to save our own resources.
content.prevOriginal: Our battles with {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} in and around {TGT_SYSTEM.name} have been a waste of resources. {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} has issued us a Trial of Possession for this small area of the conflict. content.content: Наши сражения с {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} в окрестностях {TGT_SYSTEM.name} были пустой растратой ресурсов. {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Name} объявили нам испытание владения за небольшой участок земли. Это будет битва один на один в круге равных, где вы займете наше место, как говорится, для экономии ресурсов.

content.original: Much less waste when its only two mechs facing off in the field, even less if they pay us to fight for them.
content.prevOriginal: Much less waste when its only two mechs facing off in the field, even less if they pay us to fight for them.
content.content: Гораздо меньше трат для них, когда на поле сталкиваются только два меха, и ещё меньше трат, когда за них дерёмся мы.

content.original: Destroy Duelist Warrior
content.prevOriginal: Destroy Duelist Warrior
content.content: Уничтожьте воина-дуэлянта

content.original: That is the warrior, Commander. Take them out.
content.prevOriginal: That is the warrior, Commander. Take them out.
content.content: Вот он, этот воин, командир. В расход его.

content.original: Done and done. Great job, Commander. Let's go home.
content.prevOriginal: Done and done. Great job, Commander. Let's go home.
content.content: Раз-два и готово. Отличная работа, командир. Давайте домой.

content.original: We are coming in to pick you up fast, Commander. Hold on. We will sort the fallout from this later.
content.prevOriginal: We are coming in to pick you up fast, Commander. Hold on. We will sort the fallout from this later.
content.content: Мы уже летим, командир, скоро заберём вас. Держитесь. С последствиями этого разберёмся позже.

content.original: I know they said they were going to send a proxy but, a lowly Dezgra Merc? What a waste of a perfectly good Circle of Equals.
content.prevOriginal: I know they said they were going to send a proxy but, a lowly Dezgra Merc? What a waste of a perfectly good Circle of Equals.
content.content: Я слышал, что они говорили, что пришлют доверенное лицо, но чтобы такого ничтожного дезгру, наёмника? Пустая трата времени в круге равных.

content.original: Cornered Revenge
content.prevOriginal: Cornered Revenge
content.content: Cornered Revenge

content.original: There is a Warrior in {TGT_SYSTEM.name} who refuses to back down until you, Commander, show up and fight them in a Circle of Equals. As they are Bloodnamed, we feel that you cannot brush them off as easily as some drunk in a bar. It would bring great honor to our Clan if you would arrive and show them your might.
content.prevOriginal: There is a Warrior in {TGT_SYSTEM.name} who refuses to back down until you, Commander, show up and fight them in a Circle of Equals. content.content: На {TGT_SYSTEM.name} есть воин, который отказывается отступить, пока вы, командир, не явитесь и не сразитесь с ним в круге равных. Поскольку он носит кровное имя, мы считаем, что вы не можете отмахнуться от него, как от какого-нибудь пьяницы в баре. Для нашего клана будет большой честью, если вы явитесь и продемонстрируете всем свою мощь.

content.original: Sounds like someone you may have run into before Commander. I wonder, do they write the name in blood on themselves? We should ask before the battle starts.
content.prevOriginal: Sounds like someone you may have run into before Commander. I wonder, do they write the name in blood on themselves? We should ask before the battle starts.
content.content: Похоже, будто вы с ним уже встречались, командир. Интересно, он кровное имя где-то на себе кровью пишет или что? Надо бы спросить до начала боя.

content.original: Defeat Warrior
content.prevOriginal: Defeat Warrior
content.content: Победите воина

content.original: Oh I remember this guy now, we completely humiliated them!
content.prevOriginal: Oh I remember this guy now, we completely humiliated them!
content.content: А! Я помню этого парня. Как же мы его унизили тогда!

content.original: Good work commander. Maybe that taught them a lesson
content.prevOriginal: Good work commander. Maybe that taught them a lesson
content.content: Хорошая работа, командир. Может, это его чему-нибудь научит.

content.original: Well he got his revenge, and we proved that we are only the Dezgra mercenaries he though we were.
content.prevOriginal: Well he got his revenge, and we proved that we are only the Dezgra mercenaries he though we were.
content.content: Что ж, он отомстил и доказал нам, что мы - всего лишь дезгра-мерки, как он и считал.

content.original: Never thought you'd see me again, Commander? You wouldn't have, if it wasn't for {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} making me a bondsman. I can not forgive you for what you did. Now... unlike last time - let's finish this once and for all!
content.prevOriginal: Never thought you'd see me again, Commander? You wouldn't have, if it wasn't for {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} making me a bondsman. I can not forgive you for what you did. Now... unlike last time - let's finish this once and for all!
content.content: Что, не думал, что снова увидишь меня? Ты бы и не увидел, если бы один {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.ShortName} не сделал меня бондсменом. Я не прощу тебя за то, что ты сделал. А теперь... в отличие от прошлого раза - покончим с этим раз и навсегда!

content.original: Life Lesson
content.prevOriginal: Life Lesson
content.content: Жизненый урок

Don't hold back, the pilot is going to be putting everything they learned into this fight. The Clan wants to teach some real life lessons to them, and their Sibko.
content.prevOriginal: {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} has requested we field test a new pilot from their Alpha Sibko. {COMPANY.CompanyName} has been a valuable ally and we would like our new generation to pick up some skills. content.content: {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Name} обратились к нам с просьбой провести полевые испытания нового пилота из их сибгруппы «Альфа». {COMPANY.CompanyName} были ценным союзником, и мы хотели бы, чтобы наше новое поколение подчерпнуло от вас ряд навыков. Не сдерживайте сил, пилот выложится на полную и покажет всё, чему его учили. Клан хочет преподать ему и его сибко пару уроков реальной жизни.

content.original: Some training work sounds nice about now. It's someone still learning, so how hard can it be?
content.prevOriginal: Some training work sounds nice about now. It's someone still learning, so how hard can it be?
content.content: Тренировка? Звучит неплохо. Если пилот ещё учится, то вряд ли это будет очень тяжело, верно? Верно?

content.original: Defeat the Sibko pilot
content.prevOriginal: Defeat the Sibko pilot
content.content: Одолейте пилота-сиба

content.original: There he is, Commander.
content.prevOriginal: There he is, Commander.
content.content: Вот он, командир.

content.original: This might be a real easy job but it's a job all the same. Knock him about a bit then finish things up. His Clan will be happier than he will be.
content.prevOriginal: This might be a real easy job but it's a job all the same. Knock him about a bit then finish things up. His Clan will be happier than he will be.
content.content: Может это и лёгкая работа, но это всё равно работа. Немного поколотим его и сваливаем. Его клан будет счастливее, чем он.

content.original: Getting word that the pilot has sworn revenge, and he also thanks us for the time.
content.prevOriginal: Getting word that the pilot has sworn revenge, and he also thanks us for the time.
content.content: Получил сообщение, что пилот поклялся нам отомстить, и ещё он благодарит нас за проведённое время.

content.original: Well what can you say, even young Sibko pilots are a force to deal with.

content.original:
Commander, we need you to confirm the status of a supply cache in the {TGT_SYSTEM.name} system that we established in case we need to execute local operations. Your company will run a patrol through the region, passing by the dumps and establishing communications by tightbeam only.

Do not attempt to contact the cache by radio and maintain a low profile, discretion is paramount on this operation.

content.content:
Командир, нам нужно, чтобы вы проверили состояние тайника со снабжением в системе {TGT_SYSTEM.name}, который мы создали на случай проведения местных операций. Ваша группа будет патрулировать регион, проходя вдоль свалок. Поддерживайте связь только по узконаправленному лучу.

Не пытайтесь связаться с тайником по радио и не высвечивайте, осторожность в этой операции имеет первостепенное значение.

content.original: Oh sure, dropping in a merc mech company to check your secret supply cache is the very definition of discretion. Commander, if this doesn't go sideways I may die of shock.
